summary: Weekly Playlist #2 (10/08/18-10/15/18)
body:
Weekly Playlist #2 (10/08/18-10/15/18)

Alright guys here is Weekly Playlist #2!! I know I’m a tad late on this but I’ve had a rather busy weekend and lots going on with school and work recently.

Anyways, on with the playlist!! (Again these are in no particular order.)


I Did Something Bad - Taylor Swift

Babe - Sugarland feat. Taylor Swift

End Game - Taylor Swift feat. Ed Sheeran & Future

This Is Why We Can’t Have Nice Things - Taylor Swift

Dress - Taylor Swift

Call It What You Want - Taylor Swift

Phase Me Out - VÉRITÉ

Saint - VÉRITÉ

Freedom of Falling - VÉRITÉ

Somebody Else - VÉRITÉ (The 1975 cover)


If you didn’t already know, I was lucky enough to go the Reputation Stadium Tour and see VÉRITÉ at the House of Blues this past week - hence my entire playlist this week consists solely of these two artists. I’d seen VÉRITÉ back in March - when she opened for Eden, which is when I first got into her music - and it was super cool to get to see her perform again. It was also so surreal for me to actually get to see Taylor live. I’ve loved her music since her first album came out, and she’s really the only artist that I feel like I can say I grew up with in a way.

Anyways, that concludes this weeks playlist! I hope you give some of these songs a listen if you haven’t already. Look out for next weeks playlist to drop on Monday (which will likely include Chase Atlantic and Twenty One Pilots as those are the next two shows I have coming up.)
